Experience:

2013-2019 - Entrepreneur, Sales of Medical Equipment and Related Medical Goods (ФОП Петрова С.С /МЕДТЕХНІКА)  
- Organized and supported daily operations in retail.  
- Selected and recruited employees.  
- Concluded contracts with suppliers.  
- Solved transport and logistics problems, including receipt, relocation, revaluation, and return of products to suppliers.  
- Managed accounting for payments to suppliers, contractors, buyers, and customers.  

2019-2021 - COO, Art Studio (Artichoke Art & Fashion School)  
- Led sales of short-term education courses in art direction.  
- Selected and recruited employees.  
- Organized teamwork with a focus on a team of six individuals.  
- Created and distributed tasks within teams.  
- Managed projects, including the development of monthly work plans covering various disciplines, marketing activities, and enrollment statistics for core courses.  
- Oversaw project management for weekend events, such as master classes and public talks, along with student accounting and database maintenance.  

Summary of Achievements:  
- Planned, directed, and managed multiple projects simultaneously.  
- Ensured objectives were met in alignment with outlined priorities.  
- Coordinated successful development across several initiatives.  
- Delegated responsibilities effectively and designed time schedules.  
- Negotiated contracts to ensure quality outcomes.   Google_UX_gpt4omini Score
